<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 05 at 4:12AM EST  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...Very spotty black ice possible through the morning rush...
At 410 AM, radar indicated some spotty areas of light rain. This
light rain was falling where road temperatures were in the lower
30s. It is possible for a few patches of black ice to form,
especially on bridges or overpasses until the road surface
temperatures warm above 32 by around 800 AM.
Black ice is difficult to see. Use caution if traveling in the
pre-dawn hours this morning.</description>
